						               													<description>WQRDLES is a word deduction game for two to six players, aged 10+. Each player thinks of a secret word and hides it for their opponents to guess. All players play at once - no moderator is required to host the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPONENTS&amp;#10;&amp;bull;Two or three dry erase decoding boards&amp;#10;&amp;bull;Dry erase markers&amp;#10;&amp;bull;12 query cards, each with 12 curated words&amp;#10;&amp;bull;Magnetic Covers (to hide secret words)&amp;#10;&amp;bull;2 dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INITIAL SETUP&amp;#10;1. Give each player a decoding board and a dry erase marker&amp;#10;2. Shuffle the query cards and place one card face up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;PLAY IN ROUNDS&amp;#10;At the start of each round, all players write down a secret word and cover it to keep hidden.&amp;#10;At the start of each round, clear your decoding board (except for score) and draw a new query card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAME PLAY&amp;#10;Players take turns rolling dice, selecting query words, decoding their own word, guessing each others&amp;rsquo; words.&amp;#10;On each turn &amp;hellip; &amp;#10;1. The next player rolls both dice. If doubles are rolled, proceed to the doubles action section (skipping #2)&amp;#10;2. The player selects one of the four query words matching a either die number. If all words have been used, roll again.&amp;#10;3. The player calls out the query word.&amp;#10;4. All players write down the letters of the query word in the next empty row on their decoding board.&amp;#10;5. All players decode and mark any matching letters as per the decoding section below.&amp;#10;6. All players optionally mark one of the sequence clues next to the word to indicate whether their word is alphabetically higher (&amp;gt;) or lower (&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
